Visualisation du comparatif des algorithmes

Kezhan SHI

31 mai 2014

Objectif

Lobjectif est de visualiser les prdictions des diffrents algorithmes de classification sur quelques types de relations des variables.

On utilise les packages suivants:

library(caret)
library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)
library(gridExtra)
library(reshape)
library(kernlab)

Donnes dentres

Afin de visualiser les donnes, on se limite deux variables explicatives, et une variable expliquer. Comme il sagit dun problme de classification, la variable expliquer catgorique. Ici, on se limite 2 classes.

Simulation des donnes

Dans le programme suivant, on se propose de crer trois types de sparations:

#data generation
N <- 200 # number of points per class
D <- 2 # dimensionality
K <- 3 # number of classes
X <- data.frame() # data matrix (each row = single example)
y <- data.frame() # class labels
 
set.seed(2)

forme=function(N,D,K,type){
  for (j in (1:K)){
    if (type=="spiral"){
      r <- seq(0.05,1.3,length.out = N) # radius
      t <- seq((j-1)*2*pi/3,j*2*pi/3+0.5, length.out = N) + rnorm(N, sd = 0.45) # theta
      Xtemp <- data.frame(x =r*sin(t) , y = r*cos(t)) #np.c_[r*np.sin(t), r*np.cos(t)]
      ytemp <- data.frame(matrix(j, N, 1))
    }else if(type=="lineaire"){
      Xtemp <- data.frame(x =(j-2)+rnorm(N,sd=0.3) , y = rnorm(N,sd=0.4))
      ytemp <- data.frame(matrix(j, N, 1))
    }else if(type=="circulaire"){
      r <- rep(0.05+j/K,N) +rnorm(N,sd=0.19)# radius
      t <- seq(0,2*pi, length.out = N) + rnorm(N, sd = 0.15) # theta
      Xtemp <- data.frame(x =r*sin(t) , y = r*cos(t)) #np.c_[r*np.sin(t), r*np.cos(t)]
      ytemp <- data.frame(matrix(j, N, 1))
    }
    X <- rbind(X, Xtemp)
    y <- rbind(y, ytemp)
  }
  
  data <- data.frame(X, lable = y)
  colnames(data) <- c(colnames(X), 'label')
  
  data$label <- factor(data$label)
  return (data)
}

d.spiral=forme(N,D,K,"spiral")
d.lineaire=forme(N,D,K,"lineaire")
d.circulaire=forme(N,D,K,"circulaire")

data.input=rbind(cbind(d.lineaire,type="lineaire"),
                 cbind(d.circulaire,type="circulaire"),
                 cbind(d.spiral,type="spiral"))

Il est possible de crer dautres types de sparation (par exemple, carr, ou lunaire).

Visualisation des inputs

On peut visualiser les trois sries de donnes:

p.input <- ggplot(data.input, aes(x, y,group=label,colour=label)) + 
  geom_point()+theme_bw(base_size = 20)+

Algorithmes de classification

Quelques algorithmes de classifications sont testes:

  • les donnes simules servent de base dapprentissage
  • le test se fait sur tous les points (avec un intervalle dfini) du carr qui contient lensemble des donnes dapprentissage
comparatif=function(data){

x_min=min(data$x)-0.1
x_max=max(data$x)+0.1
y_min=min(data$y)-0.1
y_max=max(data$y)+0.1

hs <- 0.05
grid <- data.frame(expand.grid(seq(x_min, x_max, by = hs), seq(y_min, y_max, by = hs)))
colnames(grid) <- c('x', 'y')

#train using different models
nnet.fit <- train(label ~ ., data=data, method="nnet",
                  tuneGrid=data.frame(size = 50, decay = 0.01), 
                  trControl=trainControl(method="cv", number=3))

svm.fit.1 <- train(label ~ ., data=data, method="svmLinear", 
                  trControl=trainControl(method="cv", number=3))

svm.fit.2 <- train(label ~ ., data=data, method="svmRadial", 
                   trControl=trainControl(method="cv", number=3))

rf.fit <- train(label ~ ., data=data, method="rf", 
                  trControl=trainControl(method="cv", number=3))

dt.fit <- train(label ~ ., data=data, method="rpart", 
                  trControl=trainControl(method="cv", number=3))

kn.fit <- train(label ~ ., data=data, method="knn", 
                  trControl=trainControl(method="cv", number=3))

models.name <- c('Plus proches voisins','Arbre de dcision',
                 'SVM linaire', 'SVM RBF kernel',
                 'Rseaux de neurones',
                 'Random forest') 

models <- list(kn.fit,dt.fit,svm.fit.1,
               svm.fit.2, nnet.fit, rf.fit)

#combine predictions on grid
pred <- grid

for (i in 1:6){
  print(i)
  Z <- predict(models[[i]], grid)
  pred <- cbind(pred, Z)

}

colnames(pred) <- c('x', 'y', models.name)

#convert from wide to long, prepare data for facet in ggplot
pred.melt <- melt(pred, id = c('x', 'y'))
colnames(pred.melt) <- c('x', 'y', 'model', 'label') 

return (pred.melt)
}

Rsultats de prdiction

lin=comparatif(d.lineaire)
cir=comparatif(d.circulaire)
spi=comparatif(d.spiral)

pred=rbind(cbind(lin,type="lineaire"),
           cbind(cir,type="circulaire"),
           cbind(spi,type="spiral"))

# save(pred,file="predictions.RData")
# load("predictions.RData")

#generate decision boundaries
dbPlot <- ggplot(data = pred)+
  geom_raster(aes(x = x, y = y,fill = as.character(label),color=as.character(label),alpha=0.3), alpha = 0.3, show.legend = F)+ 
  geom_point(data = data.input, aes(x=x, y=y, color = as.character(label)), size = 1) + 
  theme_bw(base_size = 10) + facet_wrap(~model+type,ncol=3) +
  theme(axis.ticks=element_blank(), axis.title=element_blank(),
        axis.text=element_blank(),legend.position = 'none',
        panel.grid.major = element_blank(), panel.grid.minor = element_blank())
